nality of Shakespeare's achievement. The book also includes a careful selection of items for "Further Reading."  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Apr 2020) 0aFathersxDramaxDeath. 0aHamlet (Legendary character)xDrama. 0aMurder victims' familiesxDrama. 0aPrincesxDrama. 0aRevengexDrama. 7aDRAMA / Shakespeare.2bisacsh1 aRaffel, Burton, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertYUP eBook-Package 2000-2015z978311066772108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertYale University Press eBook Package 2000-2013z978311053799440uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780300138238423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780300138238.jpg  a978-3-11-053799-4  Yale University Press eBook Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  a978-3-11-066772-1  YUP eBook-Package 2000-2015c2000d2015  aEBA_FAO  aGBV-deGruyter-alles